check.check-content:
Check the contents of user home directories for files group-owned by a group of which the home directory's owner is not a member. 1. List the user accounts. # cut -d : -f 1 /etc/passwd 2. For each user account, get a list of GIDs
        for files in the user's home directory. # find ~username -printf %G\\n | sort | uniq 3. Obtain the list of GIDs where the user is a member. # id -G username 4. Check the GID lists. If there are GIDs in the file list not present in the user list,
        this is a finding.
